<L>__{exterior courtyard dawn}
<A>__{the travelers make their departure at dawn. as the party reaches the gate, lhamo runs from the house, crying:}
<C>__{lhamo}
<D>__{wait! no!}
<A>__{the men stop. lhamo runs to the servant.}
<C>__{lhamo}
<D>__{me, too. me go, too. lhasa!}
<A>__{lhamo is in tears.}
<C>__{mother}
<D>__{no, no, no. lhasa! he always says he will travel far away. he always wants to go.}
<C>__{servant}
<D>__{we cannot, young master.}
<C>__{lhamo}
<D>__{you come back?}
<A>__{a pause.}
<C>__{servant}
<D>__{we will.}
<A>__{the travelers head down the road. mother and child return to their home, the mother carrying the boy on her hip as he swings himself around to take a last look at the strangers.}
